🔥 Difference between {% include %} and {% render %} in Shopify
✅ Short Answer (Say this in interview)
include is the older method and shares variables with the parent scope, while render is the modern and recommended method that uses isolated scope, making the code more predictable and performant.

🧠 Key Differences
🔹 1. Scope Handling
include → Shares parent variables (global access)

render → Works in isolated scope (safer)

{% assign name = "Karan" %}
{% include 'test' %}
Snippet can access name directly ❌ (not safe)

{% render 'test', name: name %}
Snippet only gets what you pass ✅ (clean)

🔹 2. Performance
include → Slower, not optimized

render → Faster, better performance

🔹 3. Maintainability
include → Can create messy dependencies

render → Clean and modular code

🔹 4. Shopify Recommendation
include → Deprecated ❌

render → Recommended ✅

💻 Example
❌ Old (include)
{% include 'product-card' %}
✅ New (render)
{% render 'product-card', product: product %}
💣 Pro Interview Line (Say this to impress)
👉 “I always use render instead of include because it ensures better scope control, avoids variable conflicts, and improves performance.”

