🧠 TRICKY LIQUID QUESTIONS (WITH PERFECT ANSWERS)
❓ 1. Why is this not working?
{% assign price = product.price %}
{% if price > 100 %}
  Expensive
{% endif %}
✅ Answer:
Shopify stores price in cents, so 100 means ₹1.
Correct comparison:

{% if product.price > 10000 %}
👉 Always remember: price is in cents

❓ 2. What will this output?
{% assign x = "5" %}
{% assign y = 5 %}

{{ x == y }}
✅ Answer:
false

👉 Because:

"5" is string

5 is number
Liquid is type-sensitive

❓ 3. Why use render over include?
✅ Answer:
render has isolated scope

Prevents variable conflicts

Better performance

include is deprecated

❓ 4. How do you pass multiple variables to a snippet?
✅ Answer:
{% render 'card', product: product, show_price: true %}
❓ 5. What is wrong here?
{% for product in collection.products %}
  {% if product.available = true %}
    In Stock
  {% endif %}
{% endfor %}
✅ Answer:
= is assignment, not comparison ❌

Correct:

{% if product.available == true %}
❓ 6. How do you limit products in loop?
✅ Answer:
{% for product in collection.products limit: 4 %}
❓ 7. How to reverse loop?
✅ Answer:
{% for product in collection.products reversed %}
❓ 8. How do you handle empty collections?
✅ Answer:
{% if collection.products.size > 0 %}
  ...
{% else %}
  No products found
{% endif %}
❓ 9. What is the difference?
{{ product.title | escape }}
{{ product.title }}
✅ Answer:
escape prevents HTML injection and renders safe text

❓ 10. Why is this bad?
{% for product in collections.all.products %}
✅ Answer:
Loads ALL products → performance issue ❌

Should use specific collection

❓ 11. How to access variant price?
✅ Answer:
{{ product.selected_or_first_available_variant.price }}
❓ 12. How to check if metafield exists?
✅ Answer:
{% if product.metafields.custom.size_chart != blank %}
❓ 13. What is blank vs empty?
✅ Answer:
blank → checks nil, empty string, empty array

empty → only arrays/strings

👉 Use blank in Shopify

❓ 14. Output first product only?
✅ Answer:
{{ collection.products.first.title }}
❓ 15. Why is this wrong?
{% assign products = collection.products %}
✅ Answer:
Works, but:

Can cause performance issues if misused

Better to loop directly

💣 ADVANCED (MOST IMPORTANT)
❓ 16. How do you prevent N+1 problem in Shopify?
✅ Answer:
Avoid nested loops

Limit product queries

Use proper collection references

Avoid repeated expensive filters

❓ 17. How to optimize image rendering?
✅ Answer:
{{ product.featured_image | image_url: width: 400 }}
Use correct size

Add loading="lazy"

❓ 18. Why avoid too many filters?
✅ Answer:
Each filter adds processing cost

Impacts performance

