metaobject use code

Here’s a clean, real-world Shopify metaobject usage (exactly how you should write in production) 💻🔥

🧠 What is Metaobject (quick)
Metaobjects = structured reusable content
Example: Size charts, FAQs, testimonials, banners

🔥 1. Access Metaobject (Single Entry)
Example: Product linked metaobject
{% assign size_chart = product.metafields.custom.size_chart.value %}

{% if size_chart != blank %}
  <div class="size-chart">
    <h3>{{ size_chart.title }}</h3>
    <p>{{ size_chart.description }}</p>
  </div>
{% endif %}
🔥 2. Metaobject with Image
{% assign obj = product.metafields.custom.feature_block.value %}

{% if obj != blank %}
  <div class="feature-block">
    <img 
      src="{{ obj.image | image_url: width: 400 }}" 
      width="400" 
      height="300" 
      alt="{{ obj.title }}"
      loading="lazy"
    >
    <h4>{{ obj.title }}</h4>
  </div>
{% endif %}
🔥 3. Loop Through Metaobject List
Example: FAQ / Features
{% assign faqs = product.metafields.custom.faqs.value %}

{% if faqs != blank %}
  <div class="faq">
    {% for item in faqs %}
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h4>{{ item.question }}</h4>
        <p>{{ item.answer }}</p>
      </div>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
{% endif %}
🔥 4. Global Metaobject (No product link)
{% assign testimonials = shop.metaobjects.testimonial.values %}

{% for item in testimonials %}
  <div class="testimonial">
    <p>{{ item.review }}</p>
    <strong>{{ item.name }}</strong>
  </div>
{% endfor %}
🔥 5. Access Specific Metaobject by Handle
{% assign obj = shop.metaobjects.testimonial["john-doe"] %}

{% if obj %}
  <p>{{ obj.review }}</p>
{% endif %}
💣 Important Points (Interview Gold)
👉 Always use .value when accessing metafield metaobject
👉 Use != blank check
👉 Use metaobjects for structured + reusable content
👉 Better than hardcoding or multiple metafields

🚀 Pro Interview Line
👉 “I use metaobjects to build scalable and reusable content structures like FAQs, size charts, and feature blocks, which clients can manage easily from Shopify admin.”

